    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Snackdown is a small collectible card game made by two friends with love for TCG, featuring over 60 unique and charming food-themed cards. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Drop Rules:</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >One Booster includes 5 Cards.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You earn 1 x Booster for every 30 minutes of playtime.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You earn 5 x Boosters once a month (Please note! You need at least 1 minute of ingame playtime to earn the drop. For that to happen you need to restart the game since it's being checked every game start.)</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Card Rarites:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Common</strong>: 65.9949%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Uncommon</strong>: 20%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Rare</strong>: 8%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>SuperRare</strong>: 5%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>UltraRare</strong>: 1%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>EpicRare</strong>: 0.005%</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>GhostRare</strong>: 0.0001%</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Card Upgrading:</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >15 Common Cards for 1 Uncommon Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >15 Uncommon Cards for 1 Rare Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >15 Rare Cards for 1 Super Rare Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >15 Super Rare Cards for 1 Ultra Rare Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >15 Ultra Rare Cards for 1 Epic Rare Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >10 Epic Rare Cards for 1 Ghost Rare Card</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Let us know what you think on our Discord! Also, we'd love to see your card collections and hear about your experiences so far. Just keep in mind: We’re just two friends creating our first standalone game. We're still at the beginning of this adventure, and yes, there will probably be bugs and mistakes. But we appreciate every bit of constructive help, like bug reports or feedback, so we can make this experience as smooth and enjoyable as possible for you. With that said—enjoy Snackdown!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
